disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Inherent Glamour.

blurb.value: Neeko can look like an ally champion. Champion combat or casting damaging spells breaks the disguise.

description.value: Innate: Neeko is offered a selection of allied champions to take their appearance. Once selected, there's a 2.5-second delay before another champion can be selected.

description2.value: While disguised, Neeko can use basic attacks while keeping her form. Taking damage from enemy champions, or casting either Blooming Burst or Tangle-Barbs or leaping by Pop Blossom breaks the illusion and puts Inherent Glamour on  cooldown.

description3.value: When disguised, Neeko can select herself to deactivate her disguise, putting Inherent Glamour on a 2-second  cooldown.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Neeko will copy aesthetics as well as superficial mechanical Statistics. She will fake a number of readings: Health bar (original's current amount becomes her apparent maximum) Secondary resource - e.g. mana, energy or none at all (original's current amount becomes her apparent maximum) Stats Buffs and debuffs with their respective icons and VFX/SFX (there are exceptions) Kill feed icon A number of attributes she actually adopts are: Default transformation toggle (non-innate) Voice lines Character interactions (jokes, taunts, dances, laughs, toggle effects), as well as their Recall animation Neeko can copy Samira's taunt animation but she will not actually throw the coin via the Taunt ability. Base movement speed Attack range (will not adopt longer attack range) Size (Only size modifiers or also base champion size?PENDING FOR TEST)

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Blooming Burst.

blurb.value: Neeko throws a seed dealing magic damage. The seed blooms again on hitting champions or killing units.

description.value: Active: Neeko propels a seed into the target area that deals magic damage to enemies hit.

description2.value: If the seed kills an enemy or damages a champion or large monster, it will bloom again after a 0.75-second delay to deal magic damage. This cannot happen more than twice per Blooming Burst.

leveling2.value: Second and Third Bloom Damage:»40 / 60 / 80 / 100 / 120 (+ 20% AP)«Total Maximum Damage:160 / 245 / 330 / 415 / 500 (+ 90% AP)

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Shapesplitter.

description.value: Passive: Basic attacks on-hit grant Neeko a stack of Shapesplitter. At 2 stacks, Neeko's next basic attack on-attack consumes the stacks to turn her attack into a non-projectile, deal bonus magic damage and grant her  bonus movement speed for 1 second.

leveling.value:
Bonus Magic Damage:50 / 70 / 90 / 110 / 130 (+ 60% AP)
Passive Movement Speed:10 / 15 / 20 / 25 / 30%

description2.value: Active: Neeko becomes invisible for 0.5 seconds, sending a temporary clone of her current form sprinting in the target direction for 3 seconds and up to 900 units away until it encounters terrain, at which it stops and remains idle. The clone is untargetable for the first 0.5 seconds.

description3.value: Both Neeko and the clone gain bonus movement speed for 3 seconds.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Tangle-Barbs.

description.value: Active: Neeko slings a magical spiral in the target direction, dealing magic damage and rooting enemies it passes through.

description2.value: If Tangle-Barbs hits at least one enemy, it thereafter grows in size and speed, with the root duration increased.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Pop Blossom.

description.value: Active: Neeko sprouts a blossom over 1.25 seconds, marking an area around her that is invisible to enemies while she is disguised.

description2.value: Neeko then shields herself for 2 seconds, increased for each enemy champion nearby, as she leaps into the air for 0.6 seconds, causing Shapesplitter clones to disappear in the process.

leveling2.value:
Shield:75 / 87.5 / 100 / 112.5 / 125 (+ 75% AP)
Bonus Shield Per Champion:»40 / 50 / 60 / 70 / 80 (+ 40% AP)«Total Shield vs. 5 Champions:275 / 337.5 / 400 / 462.5 / 525 (+ 275% AP)

description3.value: Upon landing, the blossom bursts, dealing magic damage and stunning nearby enemies for 1.25 seconds.

notes.value: * The marked area is fixed around Neeko during the delay and while leaping. Stasis will not cancel Pop Blossom and can be activated during the wind up but not during the leap. The shield amount considers clones as well. Note that the shield is not actually capped versus 5 enemy champions - if the ability hits additional clones or champions, the ability will grant additional stacks of bonus shield. This table notes the interactions during the initial delay: Attacking Allowed Abilities Allowed Movement Allowed Items Usable All items are usable Disabled N/A Interrupted by N/A Consumables Usable Spells Usable Barrier Clarity Cleanse Exhaust Ghost Heal Ignite Smite Flash Teleport Recall Hexflash Mark Dash Disabled N/A Interrupted by N/A Interrupted by Death This table notes the interactions while Neeko is leaping: Attacking Disabled Abilities Disabled Movement Disabled Items Usable N/A Disabled All items are disabled Interrupted by N/A Consumables Disabled Spells Usable Barrier Clarity Cleanse Exhaust Ghost Heal Ignite Smite Disabled Flash Teleport Recall Hexflash Interrupted by N/A Interrupted by Death, unless protected by Resurrection
